## Overview

Checkbox is a tri-state selection control: its `selection` value is `unchecked`, `checked`, or `indeterminate`, with the indeterminate value reserved for "select all" parents of a partially-selected group. It is built from a fixed 24×24 Control box that swaps a centered 16px glyph (none / check / minus) and an optional Text content zone stacking a Label above Helper text. The Figma `State` axis mixes transient interaction visuals (Hover, Focus) with persistent configuration (Error, Disabled); only the persistent states surface as the API props `isInvalid` and `isDisabled`. Color is single-mode (no theme collection) and every fill, stroke, and text color binds to a Foundations token; the only dimensional change across states is the Control border weight (1 → 2 in Hover/Focus/Error).

**Variant axes.** `State` (Default, Hover, Focus, Error, Disabled; default Default) · `Selection` (Unchecked, Checked, Indeterminate; default Unchecked) · `hasLabel` (True, False; default True). Plus the boolean property `hasHelperText` (default true).

