## API

_Confidence: high._

> Selection is a three-state value (unchecked, checked, indeterminate); indeterminate is a visual-only parent state used by 'select all' patterns and never submitted as a value. The Figma 'State' axis mixes transient interaction visuals (Hover, Focus) with persistent configuration (Error, Disabled); only the persistent states are exposed as API props (isInvalid, isDisabled) — Hover and Focus are handled by the platform at runtime. When isDisabled=true the control is non-interactive and its error styling is suppressed (isDisabled wins over isInvalid for visual treatment). hasLabel and hasHelperText are independent visibility toggles: a Checkbox may render with neither (bare control in a table cell), the label only, or both.

| Property | Type | Values | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `selection` | variant | unchecked \| checked \| indeterminate | unchecked | Checkbox value state. `indeterminate` is a parent/select-all visual only. Figma axis "Selection". |
| `isInvalid` | boolean | true \| false | false | Error/validation styling. Maps to Figma "State=Error". Pair with an external error message; the control itself shows no message text. |
| `isDisabled` | boolean | true \| false | false | Non-interactive, dimmed. Maps to Figma "State=Disabled". Suppresses error styling when also invalid. |
| `hasLabel` | boolean | true \| false | true | Renders the Label slot. Set false for bare controls in table-row, card-grid, or "select all" layouts. Figma variant "hasLabel". |
| `label` | text | (string) | Label | Only meaningful when `hasLabel` = true. Label text. |
| `hasHelperText` | boolean | true \| false | true | Renders the Helper text row beneath the label. |
| `helperText` | text | (string) | Helper text | Only meaningful when `hasHelperText` = true. Helper/description text. |

### State axis mapping

The Figma `State` axis is decomposed into the persistent API props above. Each Figma option maps to a runtime condition as follows:

| Figma `State` | `isInvalid` | `isDisabled` | Runtime condition |
|---|---|---|---|
| Default | false | false | rest |
| Hover | false | false | hovered (transient, platform-handled) |
| Focus | false | false | focused (transient, platform-handled) |
| Error | true | false | isInvalid |
| Disabled | false | true | isDisabled |

