## Structure

_Confidence: high._

> Checkbox has no size/density/shape axes — dimensions are constant. The visible box is the 24 Control frame, whose 1px border is bound to a border-color token (#1a1a1a, painted inside so the footprint stays fixed). The Selection axis is structural: it swaps the centered 16 glyph (none / check / minus) inside the constant 24 box. The State axis is a property-variant axis: the only dimensional change is the Control border weight (1 → 2 in Hover/Focus/Error, back to 1 when Disabled). hasLabel removes the entire Text content zone; hasHelperText toggles just the Helper text row. Strokes reported on the root, Content, Text content, Label, and Helper text nodes carry no paint (no border is rendered) and are not documented as borders.

