### Checkbox — Interactive states

The Control box border weight is the only dimensional property that changes across the State axis: 1 at rest and when disabled, 2 in Hover, Focus, and Error. All other dimensions are constant. Hover and Focus are transient, platform-handled visuals; Error and Disabled are the persistent API states (isInvalid, isDisabled). isDisabled suppresses error styling when both apply.

| Spec | rest | hovered | focused | error | disabled | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Control box | – | – | – | – | – | Only the border weight changes across states; box size is constant |
| ├ borderWidth | 1 | 2 | 2 | 2 | 1 | Border thickens to 2 in Hover, Focus, and Error to strengthen the affordance; returns to 1 when Disabled. Hover and Focus are transient platform-driven visuals; Error maps to isInvalid, Disabled to isDisabled |
| └ borderAlign | inside | inside | inside | inside | inside | Inside alignment keeps the 24 footprint fixed as the weight changes |

