|---|---|---|
| Announcement | "Label, unchecked, checkbox" (Checked: "Label, checked, checkbox"; Indeterminate: "Label, mixed, checkbox") | — |
| accessibilityLabel | Label | Comes from the visible Label, which merges into the checkbox — not a separate element. |
| accessibilityValue | checked / unchecked / mixed | Reflects the tri-state Selection; "mixed" is announced for Indeterminate. |
| accessibilityTraits | .isButton (toggles checked state) | Checkbox is a single interactive toggle; selected trait conveys checked. |
| accessibilityHint | Helper text (when present) | Optional Helper text merges as the hint, not a focus stop. |
| Do NOT | — | Do not read the label twice. The label merges into the stop's name; the platform must not expose the label node as a separate focusable element. |
| Do NOT | — | Do not expose the helper text as a separate focus stop. It is an accessibilityHint of this stop. |

